entity.object_description: The Audit table records when certain events, which you specify, happen to reports. This table records data for the web application and the schedulers.

column_metadata.col_description: For rows where the transactionType is Execute Report, this field joins up to two rows in the ExecutionDetail table that indicate when this execution started and, if successful, when it ended.
The companyId parameter for this event.
The application for which this action took place. The web application and schedulers are identified by their host address.
An integer used to uniquely identify each row. This is the primary key for the table.
A datetime value indicating when this event happened.
A string indicating which type of event has triggered this row to be created
The userId parameter for this event.
An integer used to join up to two rows in this table with a row in the Audit table.
A datetime value indicating when this execution started or finished, depending on the value of transactionType.
A globally unique identifier (GUID) for this execution. This GUID is used in several places throughout Exago. Notably, it is used as the file name for scheduled reports which have been saved to disk.

One of: Report Execution Begins, which indicates that the timestamp value for this row shows when this execution started. Report Execution Ends, which indicates that the timestamp value for this row shows when this execution ended.
An integer used to join a row in this table with a row in the Audit table
The file path and name of the report which the event affected.
The type of report: advanced, express, expressview, chained, dashboard

entity.object_description: The SystemStatistics table logs the available CPU load and memory for the system on which each scheduler service is installed.

column_metadata.col_description: The scheduler which was polled for system data. Every scheduler is polled at the same time. Schedulers are identified by their host address, as specified in the Administration Console.
An integer used to uniquely identify each row. This is the primary key for the table.
A datetime value indicating when this scheduler was polled.

Either CPU available, which indicates that the value field in this row shows the CPU load percentage available at this time. OR free memory, which indicates that the value field in this row shows the amount of free memory at this time.
